<paragraph blockId="87.[151,1436,690,1116]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">
<emphasis box="[198,301,970,995]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species is known only from the male. Its limited geographical range is restricted to southern Texas and just across the border into northeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[808,901,1010,1036]" name="Mexico" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Mexico</collectingCountry>
. It is a small, but easily identified, species. This species is poorly represented in collections due to its limited distribution. Approximately three dozen specimens have been examined.
</paragraph>
